Synopsis Forever alone in a crowd, failed comedian Arthur Fleck seeks connection as he walks the streets of Gotham City in 1981. Arthur wears two masks the one he paints for his day job as a clown, and the guise he projects in a futile attempt to feel like he’s part of the world around him. Arthur Fleck is isolated, bullied and disregarded by society, Fleck begins a slow descent into madness as he transforms into the criminal mastermind known as the Joker.  Starring: Joaquin Phoenix, Robert De Niro, Zazie Beetz, Marc Maron, Brett Cullen, Frances Conroy, Brian Tyree Henry and Douglas Hodge. Directed by: Todd Phillips     